/* =====================================================================
   SEASON 9 (episodes 81-90) — "The Waiting Season" (Winter)
   The long hush before spring. The two doctors finally marry, small and
   quiet, the way they love. The town waits out the deep snow, nerves and
   all. And the oldest heart in the story finishes its last round — the
   marshal is gathered home, gently, and a small gray successor takes up
   the badge, because the town raises its next heart before it ever loses
   the last. Ends on the knife-edge: the snow turns to thaw, and the baby
   decides not to wait for spring.
   VOICE RULE: every line must pass the say-it-out-loud test.
   TEACHING RULE: 8 vocab words an episode, each one lived in the story.
   ===================================================================== */

